OL,3,CRoyal Welsh Show 'more relevant than
OL,4,Cever' as it celebrates 120 years
OL,6,FDavid Davies from Pontyclun's great-
OL,7,Fgrandparents were mountain pony
OL,8,Fbreeders and competed at the very
OL,9,Ffirst Royal Welsh Show. He is the
OL,10,Fproud owner of a collection of every
OL,11,Fcatalogue from the last century
OL,12,Fthrough to 2023.
OL,14,F"It's almost like a life's obsession,"
OL,15,Fhe says.
OL,17,FAt that first show in 1904, a pony
OL,18,Fcalled Greylight won and afterwards
OL,19,Fwas sold to Australia for 1000
OL,20,Fguineas. That's the equivalent of
OL,21,F#100,000 today.
